136 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLISensorStart (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
137 {
138  bool doReconfig = true;
139  int32_t retVal = 0;
140 
141  /* Only following command syntax will be supported
142  sensorStart
143  sensorStart 0
144  */
145  if (argc == 2)
146  {
147  doReconfig = (bool) atoi (argv[1]);
148 
149  if (doReconfig == true)
150  {
151  CLI_write ("Error: Reconfig is not supported, only argument of 0 is\n"
152  "(do not reconfig, just re-start the sensor) valid\n");
153  return -1;
154  }
155  }
156  else
157  {
158  /* In case there is no argument for sensorStart, always do reconfig */
159  doReconfig = true;
160  }
161 
162  /***********************************************************************************
163  * Do sensor state management to influence the sensor actions
164  ***********************************************************************************/
165 
166  /* Error checking initial state: no partial config is allowed
167  until the first sucessful sensor start state */
168  if ((gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT) ||
169  (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_OPENED))
170  {
171  MMWave_CtrlCfg ctrlCfg;
172 
173  /* need to get number of sub-frames so that next function to check
174  * pending state can work */
175  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionConfig (&ctrlCfg);
176  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames =
177  MmwDemo_RFParser_getNumSubFrames(&ctrlCfg);
178 
179  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState() == 0)
180  {
181  CLI_write ("Error: Full configuration must be provided before sensor can be started "
182  "the first time\n");
183 
184  /* Although not strictly needed, bring back to the initial value since we
185  * are rejecting this first time configuration, prevents misleading debug. */
186  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames = 0;
187 
188  return -1;
189  }
190  }
191 
192  if (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_STARTED)
193  {
194  CLI_write ("Ignored: Sensor is already started\n");
195  return 0;
196  }
197 
198  if (doReconfig == false)
199  {
200  /* User intends to issue sensor start without config, check if no
201  config was issued after stop and generate error if this is the case. */
202  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInNonPendingState() == 0)
203  {
204  /* Message user differently if all config was issued or partial config was
205  issued. */
206  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState())
207  {
208  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided complete new configuration, "
209  "issue \"sensorStart\" (without argument) if you want it to "
210  "take effect\n");
211  }
212  else
213  {
214  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided partial configuration between stop and this "
215  "command and partial configuration cannot be undone."
216  "Issue the full configuration and do \"sensorStart\" \n");
217  }
218  return -1;
219  }
220  }
221  else
222  {
223  /* User intends to issue sensor start with full config, check if all config
224  was issued after stop and generate error if is the case. */
225  MMWave_CtrlCfg ctrlCfg;
226 
227  /* need to get number of sub-frames so that next function to check
228  * pending state can work */
229  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionConfig (&ctrlCfg);
230  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames =
231  MmwDemo_RFParser_getNumSubFrames(&ctrlCfg);
232 
233  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInPendingState() == 0)
234  {
235  /* Message user differently if no config was issued or partial config was
236  issued. */
237  if (MmwDemo_isAllCfgInNonPendingState())
238  {
239  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided no configuration, "
240  "issue \"sensorStart 0\" OR provide "
241  "full configuration and issue \"sensorStart\"\n");
242  }
243  else
244  {
245  CLI_write ("Error: You have provided partial configuration between stop and this "
246  "command and partial configuration cannot be undone."
247  "Issue the full configuration and do \"sensorStart\" \n");
248  }
249  /* Although not strictly needed, bring back to the initial value since we
250  * are rejecting this first time configuration, prevents misleading debug. */
251  gMmwMssMCB.objDetCommonCfg.preStartCommonCfg.numSubFrames = 0;
252  return -1;
253  }
254  }
255 
256  /***********************************************************************************
257  * Retreive and check mmwave Open related config before calling openSensor
258  ***********************************************************************************/
259 
260  /* Fill demo's MCB mmWave openCfg structure from the CLI configs*/
261  if (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_INIT)
262  {
263  /* Get the open configuration: */
264  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionOpenConfig (&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg);
265  /* call sensor open */
266  retVal = MmwDemo_openSensor(true);
267  if(retVal != 0)
268  {
269  return -1;
270  }
271  gMmwMssMCB.sensorState = MmwDemo_SensorState_OPENED;
272  }
273  else
274  {
275  /* openCfg related configurations like chCfg, lowPowerMode, adcCfg
276  * are only used on the first sensor start. If they are different
277  * on a subsequent sensor start, then generate a fatal error
278  * so the user does not think that the new (changed) configuration
279  * takes effect, the board needs to be reboot for the new
280  * configuration to be applied.
281  */
282  MMWave_OpenCfg openCfg;
283  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionOpenConfig (&openCfg);
284  /* Compare openCfg->chCfg*/
285  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.chCfg, (void *)&openCfg.chCfg,
286  sizeof(rlChanCfg_t)) != 0)
287  {
288  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
289  }
290 
291  /* Compare openCfg->lowPowerMode*/
292  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.lowPowerMode, (void *)&openCfg.lowPowerMode,
293  sizeof(rlLowPowerModeCfg_t)) != 0)
294  {
295  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
296  }
297  /* Compare openCfg->adcOutCfg*/
298  if(memcmp((void *)&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.openCfg.adcOutCfg, (void *)&openCfg.adcOutCfg,
299  sizeof(rlAdcOutCfg_t)) != 0)
300  {
301  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
302  }
303  }
304 
305 
306 
307  /***********************************************************************************
308  * Retrieve mmwave Control related config before calling startSensor
309  ***********************************************************************************/
310  /* Get the mmWave ctrlCfg from the CLI mmWave Extension */
311  if(doReconfig)
312  {
313  /* if MmwDemo_openSensor has non-first time related processing, call here again*/
314  /* call sensor config */
315  CLI_getMMWaveExtensionConfig (&gMmwMssMCB.cfg.ctrlCfg);
316  retVal = MmwDemo_configSensor();
317  if(retVal != 0)
318  {
319  return -1;
320  }
321  }
322  retVal = MmwDemo_startSensor();
323  if(retVal != 0)
324  {
325  return -1;
326  }
327 
328  /***********************************************************************************
329  * Set the state
330  ***********************************************************************************/
331  gMmwMssMCB.sensorState = MmwDemo_SensorState_STARTED;
332  return 0;
333 }

351 {
352  if ((gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_STOPPED) ||

355  {
356  CLI_write ("Ignored: Sensor is already stopped\n");
357  return 0;

360  MmwDemo_stopSensor();
361

363 
364  gMmwMssMCB.sensorState = MmwDemo_SensorState_STOPPED;
365  return 0;
366 }

468 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICfarCfg (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
469 {
470  DPU_CFARCAProc_CfarCfg cfarCfg;
471  uint32_t procDirection;
472  int8_t subFrameNum;
473  float threshold;
474 
475  if(MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe(argc, argv, 10, &subFrameNum) < 0)
476  {
477  return -1;
478  }
479 
480  /* Initialize configuration: */
481  memset ((void *)&cfarCfg, 0, sizeof(cfarCfg));
482 
483  /* Populate configuration: */
484  procDirection = (uint32_t) atoi (argv[2]);
485  cfarCfg.averageMode = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[3]);
486  cfarCfg.winLen = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[4]);
487  cfarCfg.guardLen = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[5]);
488  cfarCfg.noiseDivShift = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[6]);
489  cfarCfg.cyclicMode = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[7]);
490  threshold = (float) atof (argv[8]);
491  cfarCfg.peakGroupingEn = (uint8_t) atoi (argv[9]);
492 
493  if (threshold > 100.0)
494  {
495  CLI_write("Error: Maximum value for CFAR thresholdScale is 100.0 dB.\n");
496  return -1;
497  }
498 
499  /* threshold is a float value from 0-100dB. It needs to
500  be later converted to linear scale (conversion can only be done
501  when the number of virtual antennas is known) before passing it
502  to CFAR DPU.
503  For now, the threshold will be coded in a 16bit integer in the following
504  way:
505  suppose threshold is a float represented as XYZ.ABC
506  it will be saved as a 16bit integer XYZAB
507  that is, 2 decimal cases are saved.*/
508  threshold = threshold * MMWDEMO_CFAR_THRESHOLD_ENCODING_FACTOR;
509  cfarCfg.thresholdScale = (uint16_t) threshold;
510 
511  /* Save Configuration to use later */
512  if (procDirection == 0)
513  {
514  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfarCfg, MMWDEMO_CFARCFGRANGE_OFFSET,
515  sizeof(cfarCfg), subFrameNum);
516  }
517  else
518  {
519  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfarCfg, MMWDEMO_CFARCFGDOPPLER_OFFSET,
520  sizeof(cfarCfg), subFrameNum);
521  }
522  return 0;
523 }

707 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICalibDcRangeSig (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
708 {
709  DPU_RangeProc_CalibDcRangeSigCfg cfg;
710  uint32_t log2NumAvgChirps;
711  int8_t subFrameNum;
712 
713  if(MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe(argc, argv, 6, &subFrameNum) < 0)
714  {
715  return -1;
716  }
717 
718  /* Initialize configuration for DC range signature calibration */
719  memset ((void *)&cfg, 0, sizeof(cfg));
720 
721  /* Populate configuration: */
722  cfg.enabled = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[2]);
723  cfg.negativeBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[3]);
724  cfg.positiveBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[4]);
725  cfg.numAvgChirps = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[5]);
726 
727  if (cfg.negativeBinIdx > 0)
728  {
729  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid negative bin index\n");
730  return -1;
731  }
732 
733  if (cfg.positiveBinIdx < 0)
734  {
735  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid positive bin index\n");
736  return -1;
737  }
738 
739  if ((cfg.positiveBinIdx - cfg.negativeBinIdx + 1) > DPU_RANGEPROC_SIGNATURE_COMP_MAX_BIN_SIZE)
740  {
741  CLI_write ("Error: Number of bins exceeds the limit\n");
742  return -1;
743  }
744  log2NumAvgChirps = (uint32_t) mathUtils_ceilLog2(cfg.numAvgChirps);
745  if (cfg.numAvgChirps != (1U << log2NumAvgChirps))
746  {
747  CLI_write ("Error: Number of averaged chirps is not power of two\n");
748  return -1;
749  }
750 
751  /* Save Configuration to use later */
752  MmwDemo_CfgUpdate((void *)&cfg, MMWDEMO_CALIBDCRANGESIG_OFFSET,
753  sizeof(cfg), subFrameNum);
754 
755  return 0;
756 }

1234 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLIConfigDataPort (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
1235 {
1236  uint32_t baudrate;
1237  bool ackPing;
1238  UART_Params uartParams;
1239  uint8_t ackData[16];
1240 
1241 
1242  if (gMmwMssMCB.sensorState == MmwDemo_SensorState_STARTED)
1243  {
1244  CLI_write ("Ignored: This command is not allowed after sensor has started\n");
1245  return 0;
1246  }
1247 
1248  /* Populate configuration: */
1249  baudrate = (uint32_t) atoi(argv[1]);
1250  ackPing = (bool) atoi(argv[2]);
1251 
1252  /* check if requested value is less than max supported value */
1253  if (baudrate > MMWDEMO_DATAUART_MAX_BAUDRATE_SUPPORTED)
1254  {
1255  CLI_write ("Ignored: Invalid baud rate (%d) specified\n",baudrate);
1256  return 0;
1257  }
1258 
1259  /* re-open UART port if requested baud rate is different than current */
1260  if (gMmwMssMCB.cfg.platformCfg.loggingBaudRate != baudrate)
1261  {
1262  /* close previous opened handle */
1263  /* since the sensor is not running at this time, it is safe to close
1264  the existing port */
1265  if (gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle != NULL)
1266  {
1267  UART_close(gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle);
1268  gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle = NULL;
1269  }
1270 
1271  /* Setup the default UART Parameters */
1272  UART_Params_init(&uartParams);
1273  uartParams.writeDataMode = UART_DATA_BINARY;
1274  uartParams.readDataMode = UART_DATA_BINARY;
1275  uartParams.clockFrequency = gMmwMssMCB.cfg.platformCfg.sysClockFrequency;
1276  uartParams.baudRate = baudrate;
1277  uartParams.isPinMuxDone = 1U;
1278 
1279  /* Open the Logging UART Instance: */
1280  gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle = UART_open(1, &uartParams);
1281  if (gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle == NULL)
1282  {
1283  CLI_write ("Error: Unable to open the Logging UART Instance\n");
1284  return -1;
1285  }
1286  gMmwMssMCB.cfg.platformCfg.loggingBaudRate = baudrate;
1287  CLI_write ("Data port baud rate changed to %d\n",baudrate);
1288  }
1289 
1290  /* regardless of baud rate update, ack back to the host over this UART
1291  port if handle is valid and user has requested the ack back */
1292  if ((gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle != NULL) && (ackPing == true))
1293  {
1294  memset(ackData,0xFF,sizeof(ackData));
1295  UART_writePolling (gMmwMssMCB.loggingUartHandle,
1296  (uint8_t*)ackData,
1297  sizeof(ackData));
1298  }
1299 
1300  return 0;
1301 }
